11 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
12 An Act relating to militia; amending Section 1,
Chapter 453, O.S.L. 2025 (44 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
13 301B), which relates to the Oklahoma Military
Department; amending revolving fund name; amending
14 the program name; expanding purposes of use;
requiring a report; repealing Section 1, Chapter 452,
15 O.S.L. 2025 (44 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 301A), which
relates to base infrastructure needs and development;
16 providing effective dates; and declaring an
emergency.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 453, O.S.L.
21 2025 (44 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 301B), is amended to read as
22 follows:
23 Section 301B. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
24 a revolving fund for the Oklahoma Military Department to be
HB4045 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 desi gnated the "Base Infrastructure Needs and Development -
2 Technology Revolving Fund", which may also be cited as "BIND –
3 Technology Fund" "Military Readiness, Innovation, Education, and
4 Aviation Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
5 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
6 directed for deposit to the fund by law. All monies accruing to the
7 credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
8 expended by the Oklahoma Military Department for the purpose
9 established in subsection B of this section. Expenditures from said
10 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
11 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
12 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
13 payment.
14 B. There is hereby established within the Oklahoma Military
15 Department the "Base Infrastructure Needs and Development –
16 Technology Program", which may also be cited as the "BIND –
17 Technology Program" "Military Readiness, Technology, Education, and
18 Innovation Program". The Department shall utilize funds from the
19 BIND – Technology Fund Military Readiness, Innovation, Education,
20 and Aviation Revolving Fund created in subsection A of this section,
21 alone or in combination with other available funding, to make
22 infrastructure, equipment, or technology investments, including, but
23 not limited to, the purchase of licenses and software associated
24 with military simulation training, improved access onto or off a
HB4045 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 mili tary facility, construct or improve common education facilities
2 located on military bases, or to grow local industries that will
3 either:
4 1. Decrease the likelihood of military base and other military
5 infrastructure closures in this state; or
6 2. Increase the likelihood of military base and other military
7 infrastructure expansions in this state.
8 C. In fiscal years where funds are expended from the Military
9 Readiness, Innovation, Education, and Aviation Revolving Fund, the
10 Oklahoma Military Department shall file a report within forty-five
11 (45) days after the close of the fiscal year with the Governor, the
12 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro
13 Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the Appropriations and Budget
14 Chair of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, and the
15 Appropriations Chair of the Oklahoma State Senate, stating how the
16 funds were used.
17 SECTION 2. REPEALER Section 1, Chapter 452, O.S.L. 2025
18 (44 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 301A), is hereby repealed.
19 SECTION 3. Section 1 of this act shall become effective July 1,
20 2026.
21 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
22 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
23 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
24 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
